Step 1. Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities (only current liabilities here) at period-end is 624,988.48.  
• Total Owner’s Equity at period-end is 14,903,401.82.  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner’s Equity  
  = 624,988.48 / 14,903,401.82  
  ≈ 0.04193 → Rounded to 0.04

Step 2. Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• From the income statement, Net Profit is 1,903,401.82 and Total Revenue is 4,879,769.51.  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (1,903,401.82 / 4,879,769.51) × 100  
  ≈ 39.00%

Step 3. Calculate Return on Assets (ROA)  
• From the balance sheet, Total Assets at period-end is 15,528,390.30.  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100  
  = (1,903,401.82 / 15,528,390.30) × 100  
  ≈ 12.26%

Step 4. Calculate Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• The formula uses the average Accounts Receivable. Since the beginning value is 0.00 and end value is 2,984,071.72, the average = (0 + 2,984,071.72) / 2 = 1,492,035.86.  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 4,879,769.51 / 1,492,035.86  
  ≈ 3.27

Thus, the solution is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.04",
    "Net Profit Margin": "39.00%",
    "Return on Assets (ROA)": "12.26%",
    "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "3.27"
  }
}
